        "notes": "STA does NOT apply and is intentionally violated in the 'Zero Repetitions' input sequence. After the initial vector [0,0,1] fires (A*A: at least one match required), it activates both the loop body (kleene-seq1-000) and the terminal (kleene-seq1-010) simultaneously as successors. The 'Zero Repetitions' case demonstrates that [0,1,0] can arrive immediately after [0,0,1] — a HD=2 transition — and the terminal correctly matches. This is the canonical definition of 'zero or more' for the loop body: (000)* may be skipped entirely because the trigger (001)+ directly arms the terminal. Enforcing STA (requiring a [0,0,0] intermediate) would make zero-repetition semantics impossible to demonstrate. KleeneStar operates on pattern identity, not on transition topology. Important: the trigger (001) is (001)+ not (001) — the isInitial property means the trigger can re-arm successors on every match, not just once.",
        "maxHammingDistanceInDefinedSequences": 2,
